#HELPS
202 Poweritems~
Power Items in NON hero areas are limited to 1 weapon and
1 item every 50 vnums. {YALL{x power items MUST have
p-item in their name. For example, Broadsword sword p-item,
black dagger p-item.

The formula for powerweapons must be followed accordingly.

The formula is  level x 3 = points, points are used according
to the chart below.

 Point chart:
============================
1 point      = 1 mana
1 point      = 1 hp
1 point      = 5 move
5 points     = 1 save, savingbreath, savingpara, savingrod, etc.
5 points     = 1 ac
5 points     = 1 stat (str,dex,con,wis, or int)
10 points    = 1 hitroll
10 points    = 1 damroll
10 points    = vorpal, and sharp, each
20 points    = vampiric, flaming, shocking, frost, and poison, each
-10 points   = two handed

For AVdam on Power Weapons set the level 5 levels above the level you
want it to be and then type autoweapon, then set it back down, use
the level you want the weapon to be for points, not the level you used
for AVdam. Also remember to erase the stats given by autoweapon BEFORE
giving stats according to the formula.


Power Items

Power Armor

The formula for power armor is level x 4 = points. Use the chart below
to see how points are allocated. For the AC on armor set the level 5 levels
above what you are intending it to be, then autoarmor, then set it back down.
Also remember to erase autoarmor addaffects before applying new addaffects.

Power Items (Jewelry, Auras, Floating items, and Tattoos)

The formula for power items is level x 6 = points. See chart below. Remember everything but
jewelry has HALF the armor for its level, jewelry can not have AC. Jewelry includes Rings,
Earrings, and some necklaces.

Here is the point values:
============================
1 point      = 1 mana
1 point      = 1 hp
1 point      = 5 move
5 points     = 1 save, savingbreath, savingpara, savingrod, etc.
5 points     = 1 ac
10 points    = 1 hitroll
10 points    = 1 damroll
15 points    = 1 stat (1 str,dex,con,wis, or int)
